The paper deals with the recovery of missing samples in sparse signals, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for this problem, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of gradient approach and variable step size algorithm, which are common in numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the results of experiments on sparse signals with noise, which is a common problem in statistical inference and estimation, making cs.SI (Statistics) a possible sub-category.
